      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i want to make the conclusion really impactful. instead of just saying it's a policy option, how can i write it so it sounds like there's no other moral choice, like the current system is actually just inherently unjust and there's no legitimate way to defend it? i want the reader to feel like anyone who disagrees is basically defending structural racism.",
