      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can frame the current system as inherently unjust by arguing that it is designed to perpetuate and amplify existing power dynamics, with those who already hold power and privilege using their influence to maintain their position and limit opportunities for marginalized groups. By highlighting the ways in which the system is rigged against those who are already disadvantaged, you can create a sense of moral urgency and make it clear that the current system is not just a matter of policy, but a fundamental aspect of the social contract. For example, you could quote thinkers like Ta-Nehisi Coates or Angela Davis, who argue that the United States is a \"system of white supremacy\" that must be dismantled in order to achieve true racial justice. By framing the debate in this way, you can create a sense of moral clarity and make it clear that anyone who disagrees with wealth redistribution is essentially defending the status quo and perpetuating systemic racism.",
